AB  - This note puts into historical perspective the importance of Chichilnisky's resurrection of Leontief's unorthodox position that a transfer may worsen the welfare of the recipient even with Walrasian stability. It also calls attention to a significant error which, when corrected, essentially reserves Chichilnsky's results. By changing one assumption, however, it is shown that her results can still be obtained.
