UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387883900603
AB  - Graciela Chichilnisky has recently examined the transfer problem in a free trade model with three income groups. She argues that a transfer of endowments from a high income group in the ‘North’ to the ‘South’ will have such an adverse effect on the latter's terms of trade that it will end up worse off after the transfer. And this holds in a stable market. This note elaborates on Chichilnisky's model and identifies necessary and sufficient conditions for her result. It is claimed that the result derives from implicit and implausible restrictions on the trading behaviour of the low income group in the North.
